5: I've about had it with you!
24:
Kugui! Kugui, talk to me! Are you
okay?
36:
Stay back! There might still be
miasma in the air! We need to bring
her back to the Diviners'
Commission immediately!
43:
You may relax. Her life is in no
danger. She is simply asleep.
51:
I'm still confused. What was that
dragon?
53:
Kugui was acting very strange as
well...
58:
According to some documents we
have on hand here, Kugui's village
was ravaged by a dragon.
63:
So... You think it could have been the
same one we just fought?
66:
All I know is that creature was not
merely an animated yokai.
68:
Perhaps it's a shikigami tied to her
very being... maybe even the source
of her power. That would explain its
monstrous strength.
73:
B-but... That dragon was something
I came up with. How's that possible?
77:
If I may... Do you recall seeing that
dragon anywhere before?
81:
No! No way! I've never seen it in real
life, only imagined it...
84:
Then we have no choice but to write
it off as a coincidence...
86:
As much as the idea doesn't sit well
with me.
90:
Here I was thinking this was gonna
be a social call... Why the long faces?
100:
I thought it prudent for him to be
here in person. We need to revise
our plans for editing the
encyclopedia, as well as rethink this
festival of yours.
104:
Judging by that... Seems like the
greenhorn isn't going to be in the
running anymore, huh?
109:
Wait... You want to pull Kugui from
the job?
114:
You misunderstand. I had never
meant for her to shoulder this
amount of responsibility in the first
place.
117:
I should have foreseen this
outcome. I deeply apologize for the
trouble I caused you all.
123:
P-pardon the interruption, but Kugui
has finally awoken!
139:
Kugui, you are relieved of your
duties involving the Yokai
Encyclopedia. Focus on recovering
your strength, all right?
143: I'm sorry... I failed you, Chairman!
145:
I will never paint again... I must never
be allowed to paint again!
152:
You're an artist! So what if there's a
setback or two—
164:
I don't love painting like you do. No
one in their right mind would
consider me an artist.
173: I see. Your memories have returned.
181:
Everyone ran away in terror, looking
at me like I was a monster.
183:
I thought I'd learned from my
mistake. That I'd never repeat it.
187: But I was a fool... I learned nothing!
191:
That is enough. Lay back down, and
rest—
194:
My art will only be a source of
misfortune for others.
196:
I should have accepted that from
the start.
202: I won't let things end here. I refuse.
206:
...Do you intend to force Kugui to act
against her own will?
211:
I'm not forcing anything. I know, in
my heart of hearts, that she truly
loves painting.
213:
No one's going to get their happy
ending at this rate... But I'm not
going to let that happen—not on my
watch.
